<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[189,1399,917,1262]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Some authors, e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Nesi" box="[420,685,917,944]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Nesi" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="544 - 554" refId="ref270530" refString="Nesi N., Nakoune E., Cruaud C. &amp; Hassanin A. 2011. DNA barcoding of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Pteropodidae). The mitochondrial genome does not provide a reliable discrimination between Epomophorus gambianus and Micropteropus pusillus. Comptes Rendus Biologies 334 (7): 544 - 554. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. crvi. 2011.05.003" type="journal article" year="2011">
Nesi 
<emphasis box="[481,540,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
(2011: 547)
</bibRefCitation>
, consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[804,946,918,943]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crypturus">
<emphasis box="[804,946,918,943]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. crypturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1006,1164,917,943]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1164,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. gambianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to differ at the subspecific level only. However, they admit that several recent classifications suggest they differ at the species level. 
<bibRefCitation author="Claessen &amp; De Vree" box="[258,632,988,1014]" firstAuthor="Claessen" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="177 - 186" refId="ref258297" refString="Claessen C. J. &amp; De Vree F. 1990. Systematic and distributional notes on the larger species of the genus Epomophorus Bennet, 1836 (Chiroptera: Pteropodidae). In: Peters G. &amp; Hutterer R. (eds) Vertebrates in the Tropics. Proceedings of the International Symposium on Vertebrate Biogeography and Systemematics in the Tropics, Bonn, June 5 - 8, 1989: 177 - 186. Museum Alexander Koenig, Bonn." type="journal article" year="1990">Claessen &amp; De Vree (1990: 180)</bibRefCitation>
indicate that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[787,945,988,1014]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">
<emphasis box="[787,945,988,1014]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. gambianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only occurs in the tropical savanna and woodland zones from 
<collectingCountry box="[448,538,1023,1049]" name="Senegal" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Senegal</collectingCountry>
to the 
<collectingCountry box="[621,913,1023,1049]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[926,997,1023,1049]" name="Sudan" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Sudan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1056,1155,1023,1049]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[1168,1310,1024,1049]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crypturus">
<emphasis box="[1168,1310,1024,1049]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. crypturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the other hand, only occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[482,572,1058,1084]" name="Zambia" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Zambia</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[683,785,1058,1084]" name="Tanzania" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[939,1001,1059,1085]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">DRC</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nesi" box="[1010,1258,1058,1085]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Nesi" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="544 - 554" refId="ref270530" refString="Nesi N., Nakoune E., Cruaud C. &amp; Hassanin A. 2011. DNA barcoding of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Pteropodidae). The mitochondrial genome does not provide a reliable discrimination between Epomophorus gambianus and Micropteropus pusillus. Comptes Rendus Biologies 334 (7): 544 - 554. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. crvi. 2011.05.003" type="journal article" year="2011">
Nesi 
<emphasis box="[1068,1122,1059,1085]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
(2011: 547)
</bibRefCitation>
furthermore add 
<collectingCountry box="[240,390,1094,1120]" name="Mozambique" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
and eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[541,600,1094,1120]" name="South Africa" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">RSA</collectingCountry>
. As all of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ogilby" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[768,927,1094,1120]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gambianus">
<emphasis box="[768,927,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. gambianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[1339,1398,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 23
</bibRefCitation>
, map 6) are from the southernmost part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[819,881,1129,1155]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">DRC</collectingCountry>
, these should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[1202,1341,1130,1155]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crypturus">
<emphasis box="[1202,1341,1130,1155]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. crypturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The distribution map shows that all of the specimens currently assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[992,1132,1165,1190]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crypturus">
<emphasis box="[992,1132,1165,1190]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">E. crypturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are from the provinces of Haut-Katanga, Haut-Lomami and Lualaba, with one exception: RMCA 31557, a subadult female from Luluabourg (= Kananga) in Kasaï-Central Province. This specimen might need to be re-examined.
</paragraph>
